OL,3,CThousands attend anti-racism rally in
OL,4,CBelfast
OL,6,FThousands of people have attended an
OL,7,Fanti-racism rally in Belfast following
OL,8,Fdays of unrest provoked by a knife
OL,9,Fattack.
OL,11,FOrganised by the Unite Against Racism
OL,12,Forganisation, the Together Against
OL,13,FHate rally is taking place outside
OL,14,FBelfast City Hall.
OL,16,FIt follows days of violent
OL,17,Fdemonstrations held across the city in
OL,18,Fthe wake of a stabbing attack which
OL,19,Fsaw Stephen Ogilvie lose his eye and
OL,20,Fsuffer deep cuts to his head, face and
OL,21,Fback.
